na</i> ‘spring, stream’."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Alice Leybourne was born about 1249, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with Philip de Neville."},"et":{"Abt 1249–":"umbes 1249–Surnud","1247–Male":"1247–Surnud","1266–1314":"1266–1314","1268–Female":"1268–Surnud","1249–Female":"1249–Surnud","1249":"1249","1314":"1314","1247":"1247","1268":"1268","Abt 1266":"umbes 1266","1266":"1266","Abt 1249":"umbes 1249","Abt 1268":"umbes 1268","Of, Brampton, Lincolnshire, England":"Brampton, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of,, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1249–":"noin 1249–Kuollut","1247–Male":"1247–Kuollut","1266–1314":"1266–1314","1268–Female":"1268–Kuollut","1249–Female":"1249–Kuollut","1249":"1249","1314":"1314","1247":"1247","1268":"1268","Abt 1266":"noin 1266","1266":"1266","Abt 1249":"noin 1249","Abt 1268":"noin 1268","Of, Brampton, Lincolnshire, England":"Brampton, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of,, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1249–":"environ 1249–Décédée","1247